First combine over the common denominator \(x+5\):  
\[
\frac{x^2+8x}{x+5}+\frac{15}{x+5}
=\frac{x^2+8x+15}{x+5}
=\frac{(x+3)(x+5)}{\,x+5\,}
=\;x+3,\quad x\neq -5.
\]

First put both fractions over the common denominator \,(x+3)(x−4)\,.  Since   
g(x)=\frac{x+17}{x^2−x−12}=\frac{x+17}{(x+3)(x−4)},   
and   
f(x)=\frac{x+1}{x+3}=\frac{(x+1)(x−4)}{(x+3)(x−4)}=\frac{x^2−3x−4}{(x+3)(x−4)},   
we get   

R(x)=f(x)−g(x)=\frac{x^2−3x−4}{(x+3)(x−4)}−\frac{x+17}{(x+3)(x−4)}   
=\frac{x^2−3x−4−(x+17)}{(x+3)(x−4)}   
=\frac{x^2−4x−21}{(x+3)(x−4)}   
=\frac{(x−7)(x+3)}{(x+3)(x−4)}   
=\frac{x−7}{x−4},   

with the understanding that x≠−3,4 (those were excluded by the original denominators).
